item.title: I was bored so made this
item.dc:creator: @leacher1197 leacher1197
item.description:
@leacher1197 wrote:

[quote=“Frell, post:12, topic:293659”][quote author=Javacisnotrecognized link=topic=388562.msg2904526#msg2904526 date=1249713942]

There was never any evidence the letter ‘I’ resembled a specific value therefore it is a letter. A useless letter may not be used in math unless it is waiting to be assigned or already assigned.

Lets say I was 2. The banner would be horribly ruined due to the mathematics that were included with the second statement:

Mopar2sTheBest
2 < 3 Mopar
Banner by leacher1197

Moe - par - toos - the best.
No such thing. Case closed gf

Any moron could tell that he’s using dynamic typing. In the first statement, it’s the letter ‘I’; in the second, it’s obviously the Roman numeral for one.
[/quote]
I laughed so hard, lol.

Indeed it could represent the Roman numeral. This calls for drastic measures. We’re going to need all the mods here and find out what this ‘I’ means, this could risk the forums…

…

… the mitb side …

:eek:[/quote] I can’t beleive that this topic brought so many Mods here, I was expecting for someone to say good job (and someone did) But I didn’t expect a whole load of mods to start posting
